title: prompt for post-mortem
pid: c1e5f026-b09a-4d3b-981e-bc07deb8df13
body: |2-
  Welcome, Claude! Please read coding-advice/ORIENTATION.org, and whatever it refers to (recursively), for orientation.

  Then, please read all of TODO/local-view-update/. It's maybe verbose but it gives the story of what's happened since this branch diverged from main.

  Your mission is to evaluate that work.
  It's a huge job and I have no idea how to modularize it; do whatever you think is smart.
  My concerns are:
  - completeness: Did we actually do everything we intended to do?
    This includes not just the original plan but later ideas that came up.
  - elegance: Do any of these solutions feel awkward, inefficient,
    or otherwise worth revisiting?
  - clarity: Are the names good? Bear in mind that I prefer clear, verbose names
    to terse ones. Also I mix camelcase and snake case,
    so that compound words like _inRustGraph_ can look like one token,
    which can make names much clearer. (For instance, if we write _in_rust_graph_
    instead, that looks like an adjective phrase, when in fact it is a noun.
    Sometimes it is similarly clarifying to camel-case
    adjective or verb phrases into a single underscore-bracketed token.)

  I have not listed correctness, although if you do find any incorrectness,
  please include it in your report.

  Please write up what you find in TODO/local-view-update/review.org.
